lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Reaction from Democratic challengers to President Donald Trump's State of the Union address:
headline_main: Democratic Challengers Weigh In on State of the Union Speech
headline_print_headline: Democratic Challengers Weigh In on State of the Union Speech

abstract: President Trump used his annual address as an attempt to gain some ground with black voters, a group that largely believes he is widening a racial divide in the United States.
snippet: President Trump used his annual address as an attempt to gain some ground with black voters, a group that largely believes he is widening a racial divide in the United States.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As President Trump delivered his State of the Union address on Tuesday, he highlighted several people of color for promotions and giveaways and referred to policies popular with minority voters.

abstract: No doubt that the Trump administration is closer to a peace settlement with the Afghan Taliban than any previous administration. President Trump has also promised a complete troop withdrawals from Afghanistan, though he has yet to order it. But since May, Mr. Trump has actually deployed more than 14,000 troops to the Middle East to deter Iran from potential attacks and to safeguard American forces and bases. The partial troop withdrawal from Syria last fall was just that, partial.

President Trump has also promised a complete troop withdrawals from Afghanistan, though he has yet to order it. But since May, Mr. Trump has actually deployed more than 14,000 troops to the Middle East to deter Iran from potential attacks and to safeguard American forces and bases. The partial troop withdrawal from Syria last fall was just that, partial.
headline_main: “As we defend American lives, we are working to end America’s wars in the Middle East.”

abstract: Real median household income is now at its highest levels. And average hourly earnings growth has accelerated under President Trump for manufacturing workers, outpacing inflation. But employment growth in manufacturing, which Mr. Trump promoted in his speech last year, slowed to fewer than 50,000 jobs in 2019 — the worst rate of his presidency and the second worst of the long recovery from recession. And job growth has slowed sharply — from 2.6 percent at the start of 2019 to 1.3 percent at the end of the year — in so-called middle-wage sectors that include mining, construction and transportation.

But employment growth in manufacturing, which Mr. Trump promoted in his speech last year, slowed to fewer than 50,000 jobs in 2019 — the worst rate of his presidency and the second worst of the long recovery from recession. And job growth has slowed sharply — from 2.6 percent at the start of 2019 to 1.3 percent at the end of the year — in so-called middle-wage sectors that include mining, construction and transportation.
headline_main: “This is a blue-collar boom. Real median household income is now at the highest level ever recorded.”
